This species seems recently to have expanded its range in northeastern Europe. It had not been recorded from Estonia until 2010, but is now widespread in the country (
Sammet et al. 2018
). It is also a newcomer in the fauna of Latvia where it is now common in a variety of habitats ( Spuņģis 2010 ). The first record from Russia outside the Kaliningrad region was from a park in Moscow and is probably due to a recent introduction ( Golovatch & Matyukhin 2011 ).
